        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 6:02PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 602 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Ararat, or near Dobson, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fairview...
Dobson...
Pilot Mountain...
Mountain Park...
King...
Level Cross...
and Pinnacle.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for
north central and northwestern North Carolina...and south central and
southwestern Virginia.</instruction>
